laboratory_examinations.findings: Aspartate aminotransferase: 960 U/liter, Alanine aminotransferase: 347 U/liter; elevated levels indicating acute liver failure.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Liver function tests 2 months prior were normal (19 U/liter for both aspartate and alanine aminotransferase). After discontinuing lamotrigine, aspartate aminotransferase levels returned to normal within 5 days, and alanine aminotransferase levels remained mildly elevated at 102 U/liter.
